dataIdInfo.idAbs:
Table providing detailed descriptions of the U.S. Census Bureau's Master Address File/Topologically Integrated Geographic Encoding and Referencing (MAF/TIGER) database Feature Class Codes (MTFCC). The MAF/TIGER Feature Class Code (MTFCC) replaces the old CFCC code that was used in the 2000 Census. It is more generalized than the CFCC, but still represents a means of differentiating similar feature types.

Because of table character limitations, the feature class description field (DESCRIPT) may be truncated for particularly verbose descriptions. With regards to the TIGER roads, the table's primary utility will be in identifying distinctions in the different road types (MTFCC codes that start with "S").

From Appendix F in http://www.census.gov/geo/www/tiger/tgrshp2010/TGRSHP10SF1.pdf.

Consts.useLimit: No limitations, although this table is still considered DRAFT by MassGIS.
